title: Disney TV Movie - Danny the Champion of the World (1989)
description:
Looked for this movie for quite a while and finally found it. Unfortunately there are Dutch subs throughout the movie. To my knowledge this movie has yet to come out on DVD and the subtitles don&#039;t really detract from the quality of this rare movie. Film is based on a book by Roald Dahl, the man behind Charlie and the Chocolate Factory. Enjoy

Somewhere in England, in the Autumn of 1955, a widowed father and his son live an idyllic life together. Only their gas station happens to sit on a piece of land that a local developer wants to buy. And when he won&#039;t take no for an answer, and sets government inspectors and social works onto Danny and his father, Danny and his father decide to get even with Hazell and his pheasant- shooting friends in a manner in keeping with their own family tradition.
